    <h1 class="mb-4">Perplexity vs ChatGPT for UK Businesses</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 | Rank4AI research</p>
    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0">Perplexity excels at real-time research with citations whilst ChatGPT offers superior creative and analytical capabilities for UK businesses.</p>
    </div>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">UK businesses face a crucial choice between two leading AI tools. Perplexity and ChatGPT serve different purposes. Understanding their strengths helps you pick the right tool for your needs.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">How They Source Information</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity acts like a real-time search engine with AI capabilities. It scans the web continuously. The platform pulls information from current websites, news sources, and databases. This means you get the latest information available online.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT works differently. It relies on training data with a knowledge cutoff. The model doesn't browse the internet in real-time. Instead, it draws from patterns learned during training. This approach offers consistent responses but may miss recent developments.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Citation Behaviour</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity shines with citations. Every response includes numbered references. You can click through to original sources. This transparency builds trust and allows fact-checking. UK businesses value this accountability for compliance and accuracy.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT rarely provides citations. It generates responses without linking to sources. This makes verification challenging. However, recent versions allow web browsing when specifically requested. The citation format remains inconsistent compared to Perplexity.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Best Use Cases for UK Businesses</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Perplexity works best for research tasks. Market analysis, competitor research, and regulatory updates suit this tool. UK businesses benefit from its ability to find current information about legislation changes. The citation feature helps with due diligence and fact-checking.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT excels at creative and analytical work. Content creation, strategy development, and problem-solving are its strengths. UK businesses use it for writing marketing copy, analysing complex scenarios, and brainstorming solutions. The conversational interface makes it ideal for iterative work.</p>

